Three malnourished guinea pigs have been found dead behind a bus shelter in Aberdeenshire.The Scottish SPCA said the pets were discovered inside a plastic bag on Westhill Road, Westhill, on Monday morning by a member of the public.The animal charity said one of the guinea pigs was all white, one was white with a black patch on its head and the third was black, tan and white.Scottish SPCA inspector Fiona Mackenzie said: "A post mortem was carried out and found that all three guinea pigs were in a malnourished state."She urged anyone with information to contact its confidential animal helpline.
